  <static seed="218" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticEquations/solveQuad355.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>{\left(x+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+6x+8\right)} = 0</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="20" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{-2,-4,-3\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that this is <em>not</em> a quadratic equation, as its degree is <m>3</m>. However, 
the factoring technique still applies</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {\left(x+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+6x+8\right)} = 0 \amp \Rightarrow {\left(x+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+4\right)}=0\\
                                \amp \Rightarrow x=-2\text{ or } x=-4 \text{ or }x=-3\\
        \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Each solution can be checked by substituting it into the original equation- this is left as an exercise.</p>
</solution>
